<item>
            <title>[LU-5993] gerrit losing google sign in  capability April 20, 2015</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5993</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Google is shutting down OpenID 2.0 support on April 20, 2015, and instead offering OAuth 2.0 (OpenID Connect).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre gerrit users that employ Google for sign in are starting to see this message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/6135882&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/6135882&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More details are here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://developers.google.com/accounts/docs/OpenID&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://developers.google.com/accounts/docs/OpenID&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hopefully the gerrit folks will support the new authentication method soon, and we will then need to upgrade Lustre&apos;s gerrit instalation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
