                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="107484" author="adilger" created="Fri, 20 Feb 2015 14:37:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According to the Gerrit developers, OpenID Connect will not be supported, so anyone using google for their OpenID login will need to find another OpenID provider.  Examples of other OpenID providers given:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://help.launchpad.net/YourAccount/OpenID&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://help.launchpad.net/YourAccount/OpenID&lt;/a&gt; It was pointed out that the OpenStack project requires you to use Launchpad as your OpenID provider. Probably prevents people from the mistake of &quot;Which OpenID did I use?&quot; and thus creating duplicate accounts.&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;http://fedoraproject.org/wiki/OpenID&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://fedoraproject.org/wiki/OpenID&lt;/a&gt; for those that may have Fedora credentials; probably not many Lustre contributors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, unless somebody writes an OpenID Connect plugin for Gerrit (possible, but there is nothing in progress right now) we will need to have all Google users migrate to another OpenID provider.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="100903" author="pjones" created="Sat, 6 Dec 2014 13:47:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Chris&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll look into this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
